## Notes

- Every resolved question MUST cite the PRD section it updates so a
  reviewer can trace the answer back to a normative requirement.
- `agt-clarify` refuses to mark a question Resolved without a `Decided
  by` value; ambiguity here defeats the purpose of the clarify phase.
- Deferred entries do NOT silently drop — they live in the PRD's
  `## Open Questions` and surface again in `agt-plan` as either a Plan
  decision or a follow-up clarify pass.
